  "description": "This part replaces a Zome ball where you need to have two yellow lines intersecting, lying in the green plane. Its purpose is aesthetic, when you don&#039;t want to use a ball to make the junction. This might happen if you&#039;re trying to represent a mathematical object wherein balls should represent vertices, not false vertices arising from edge intersections.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTwelve copies are modeled as a single print, with small sprues connecting the individual bobs. They can be twisted apart, then cleaned up with a sharp knife or nail clippers.",
